%h2 Class05 Answer:
%h2 Install Nvidia CUDA v8.0 Software

%p I followed the steps in this page on my Ubuntu 16 laptop.

%p Why do we want CUDA v8.0 ?

%p I want to install Nvidia CUDA v8.0 Software because TensorFlow r1.2 asks for that.

%p As of 2017-06-29, TensorFlow shows these instructions:

%img(src='/class05/tf12cuda.png')
%hr/

%p Next I studied the content at this URL:

%p
  %a(href='http://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-installation-guide-linux/#axzz4VZnqTJ2A' target='x')
    http://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-installation-guide-linux/#axzz4VZnqTJ2A

%p I saw this:

%img(src='/class05/cuda8a.png')

%p In the above page I completed the pre-installation actions:

.syntax
  %pre
    %code
      lspci | grep -i nvidia
      uname -m && cat /etc/*release
      gcc --version
      sudo apt-get install linux-headers-$(uname -r)
%p The above page asked me to choose an installation method.
%p It asked me to specify my choice at this URL:
%p
  %a(href='https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads' target='x')
    https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads

%p I captured a screen-shot of the above page:

%img(src='/class05/cudaDL1.png')
%hr/

%p You can see my choices in the dark-green boxes below:

%img(src='/class05/cudaDL2.png')
%hr/

%p I downloaded the base installer via the button at the bottom.

%p The link of that button is listed below:

%p
  %a(href='https://developer.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/8.0/Prod2/local_installers/cuda-repo-ubuntu1604-8-0-local-ga2_8.0.61-1_amd64-deb' target='x')
    https://developer.nvidia.com/compute/cuda/8.0/Prod2/local_installers/cuda-repo-ubuntu1604-8-0-local-ga2_8.0.61-1_amd64-deb

%p Next I studied the content at this URL:
%p
  %a(href='http://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-installation-guide-linux/#ubuntu-installation' target='x')
    http://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-installation-guide-linux/#ubuntu-installation

%p I summarize that content into shell commands listed below:

.syntax
  %pre
    %code.bash
      sudo dpkg -i ~/Downloads/cuda-repo-ubuntu1604-8-0-local-ga2_8.0.61-1_amd64.deb
      sudo apt-get update
      sudo apt-get install cuda

%p I ran the above shell commands.

